rComments: Great Professor. She is new at teaching, but she makes up for it in her dedication to her students.  She marked my essay outline and provided me with a DETAILED guideline on how I can make my essay better (even suggesting books, and the pages I can find quotes on).  Also any questions about the essay or test- she is more than willing to answer.

She is a phd student and is the reason why U of O should stop using PHD students to teach. Poor teacher. Failed to prepare us for the Midterms. Asks critical questions that are ambigous, that require lenghty answers in exams, and  that she herself cannot answer. She is very unhelpful too.
